<seg id=1> Irish Republican Army Announces Ceasefire </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE London, Aug. 31 (Li Wenhao reporting):  The Irish Republican Army announced today that beginning from midnight tonight the organization would cease all military action completely, implementing an "unconditional and unlimited" ceasefire. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In a statement released by the IRA to the English and Irish news media, the organization made the above decision in light of current trends and in order to advance the peace process in Northern Ireland. It has informed all groups within the organization as well. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The statement requests that the English government face up to its own responsibility. It urges each side to firmly and patiently face the new developments brought about by this ceasefire and to hold broad talks with the major political parties in England, Ireland and Northern Ireland, with a view to finally resolving the conflict in Northern Ireland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The statement says that the IRA's ceasefire provides an opportunity for a "just and lasting resolution" to the problems in Northern Ireland. </seg>
<seg id=6> But the IRA also reiterated that it still abides its "republican goals", meaning the unification of the whole island of Ireland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The IRA has undergone a 25-year violent uprising in Northern Ireland in order to bring about the unification of Northern Ireland and the Irish Republic. </seg>
</p>
